A Brazilian physician, journalist, politician, professor, novelist, poet, playwright and memorialist, Joaquim Manuel Macedo is the patron of chair 20 of the Academia Brasileira de Letras. His work is extensive and is still a great success to this day. His great literary importance lies in the fact that is considered one of the founders of Brazilian novels.
